news.title: Land acquisition for Kochi Metro extension awaits government fund
news.para: As per the estimate, around Rs 105 crore is needed for acquiring land required for widening the road along Palarivattom-Infopark stretch through which the alignment of the Metro extension passes.

news.title: Jalandhar: Latifpura residents reject government offer on 2-BHK flats
news.para: The offer was announced by two AAP MLAs on Wednesday evening. The displaced residents said they had better spaces and there was no point in shifting to a distant and smaller place.

news.title: Pune: New panel to look into levy issues in nine merged areas
news.para: Shivtare on Thursday held a meeting with municipal commissioner Vikram Kumar and civic officials to discuss the various problems being faced by residents of 11 villages in the last four years.

news.title: Six get Bhopal civic body's notice for malpractice and illegal building permission
news.para: Malpractice by the authorized architect and structural engineers was for eight building permits in Panchawati Colony, Pragati Nagar Panchwati Extension Singarcholi.

news.title: Ambuja & ACC cement plants in Himachal Pradesh to close
news.para: The ACC plant in Barmana and Ambuja plant in Darlaghat, owned by the Adani group, had announced their closure on Wednesday.

news.title: Soon, property owners can calculate and verify tax bills in Pune
news.para: Annual ratable value (ARV) is a base price on the basis of which the property tax is calculated. This information will be provided offline at the department’s office in Shivajinagar as well as on the PMC’s website with the formula to calculate tax.

news.title: Nashik civic body serves notices to 75,000 property tax defaulters
news.para: The defaulters include 15 to 20 government establishments and commercial and residential property owners. These defaulters have property tax dues pending for the past few years.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram civic body proposes online-only payment of property tax above Rs 50,000
news.para: s per the proposal, initially, tax dues above Rs 50,000 can be paid only via online. The slab will then be modified to cover tax payments above Rs 10,000. Online-only payment of tax above Rs 10,000 is likely to be introduced from January 2023.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Builders buy two plots for Rs 640 crore
news.para: Both the plots are on the high FSI zone of 5.4 and will have commercial and residential projects respectively. The plot in the Science City area will see the biggest residential iconic project of the city with a built-up area of around 20 lakh sq feet.

news.title: Tardy execution of MahaRERA recovery orders irks consumers
news.para: Statistics available on MahaRERA website revealed that 773 recovery warrant orders from 13 districts in the state have been issued against 302 projects in the state till August 2022.

news.title: Mumbai: BDD chawls' residents can take Rs 25,000 rent if not keen on transit home
news.para: Anil Diggikar, Mhada chief executive officer and vice-president, said that the state government has approved a proposal that will allow rent to be paid to the tenants who have to be shifted out to carry out redevelopment of the chawls.

news.title: Gurugram: 15 illegal colonies built on agricultural land demolished
news.para: On Thursday, the team cleared an unauthorised colony having an area of around three acres near the revenue estate of Budhera village.

news.title: Supreme Court junks Supertech plea over 'settlement' order
news.para: The company's account was classified as NPA in 2018 after it could not repay a loan of Rs 678 crore that was disbursed by the consortium of lenders comprising Union Bank of India, Bank of Maharashtra, Central Bank of India and Oriental Bank of Commerce for the 'Supernova' project in Noida, Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Zara founder buys Seattle skyscraper for $323 million
news.para: The purchase follows a $500-million investment in a 64-floor skyscraper of luxury apartments in New York's Financial District.

news.title: China's new home prices fell for fourth month in November 2022
news.para: New home prices fell 0.2% from October, the fourth straight decline, and by 1.6% from a year earlier, the seventh on-year drop, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.
